1 (ii) one representative of the League of Women Voters of Maryland;
2 (iii) one representative of the National Federation of the Blind,
3 Maryland;
4 (iv) one representative of the Arc of Maryland;
5 (v) one representative of the Maryland Developmental Disabilities
6 Council;
7 (vi) an expert in voting accessibility;
8 (vii) an expert in election security; and
9 (viii) an expert in cybersecurity.
10 (c) The Governor shall designate the chair of the Workgroup.
11 (d) The State Board of Elections shall provide staff for the Workgroup.
12 (e) A member of the Workgroup:
13 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Workgroup; but
14 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
15 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
16 (f) The Workgroup shall:
17 (1) examine the current processes and procedures in the State relating to
18 mail–in ballot return;
19 (2) assess the impact on voters with disabilities of requiring mail–in ballots
20 to be returned in paper form;
21 (3) collect information about current practices and standards for accessible
22 alternatives to paper mail–in ballot return in other jurisdictions;
23 (4) evaluate alternatives to paper mail–in ballot return for individuals with
24 disabilities, including each of the following considerations:
25 (i) accessibility;
26 (ii) security, including options for mitigating security concerns;
27 (iii) the potential for discrimination against voters with disabilities;

